The paper deals with the design of transmission policies for energy harvesting wireless networks, which involves optimization of the short-term throughput and minimization of the transmission completion time under energy causality and battery capacity constraints. This problem is related to information theory and networked systems, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.IT and cs.NI, respectively. The paper also considers the power-rate relationship and the concavity of the function, which are topics in mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The algorithmic approach to finding the optimal transmission policy falls under the sub-category cs.SY, while the numerical results and simulations are related to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
